<ul>
<li>
Wait()
<br>Makes you wait a turn.</li>
<li>Move()
<br>Makes you move 1 square, in the direction you facing.
</li><li>Rotate(string Direction)
<br>Makes you turn 90 degrees in the given direction, that is either "RIGHT" or "LEFT".
</li><li>Shoot()
<br>Makes you shoot a bullet the direction you facing that travels with one square per turn and destroyes other bullets, and damages enemy robots for 1 health.
</li><li>What_I_See()
<br>This method returns that what your robot's sensor can see, it returns the first non-air square's distance and type in the direction you are facing.  It returns these information as a 'See' class defined like this: 
<code>
<br>public static class see {
<br><tab1>    public int what;</tab1>
<br><tab1>    public int howFar;</tab1>
<br>
<br><tab1>    public see(int a, int b) {</tab1>
<br><tab1>        what = b;</tab1>
<br><tab1>        howFar = a;</tab1>
<br><tab1>    }</tab1>
<br>}
</code>
</li><li>getHealth()
<br>Returns the health of your robot as an integer. 
</li><li>getPlayerX()
<br>Returns the X coordinate of your robot as an integer.
</li><li>getPlayerY()
<br>Returns the Y coordinate of your robot as an integer.
</li><li>getStartingMap()
<br>Returns the map as a 6 by 6 primitive int array where 0 means that the given square is empty and 1 that there is a wall, that blocks movement.</li>
